title: Badgers' loss to Hawkeyes adds to AP Top 25 shakeup
text:
Updated Oct 4, 2015 at 3:11p ET 
Wisconsin fell out of The Associated Press college football Top 25 after a loss to Iowa on Saturday. 
Iowa jumped onto the list at No. 22, their first time in the ranking since November 2010. The Badgers were ranked No. 19 last week. 
Ohio State remained No. 1, while No. 2 TCU and No. 3 Baylor edged forward, No. 4 Michigan State slipped and No. 5 Utah and No. 6 Clemson took big jumps. 
No. 13 Northwestern and No. 18 Michigan brought the Big Ten's total in the poll to five, one fewer than the SEC and tied with Pac 12. THE AP TOP 25 POLL, WEEK 6 
1. Ohio State (5-0)
